inculde index.js in home.js

in home.js use require statement 
:require('path);
in index.js 
:module.exports=objectname

In node js there is concept of module wrapper function
(function(export,require,module,filename,dirname)
{
//code of index.js or home.js
})
the above is already defined no need to explicitly define above function,you can use parameters directly
there are various module which is in-built  like os,path module to check freememory etc 
